The Cybersecurity Bootcamp at 4Geeks Academy is a 16-week program designed to help individuals become cybersecurity specialists. No prior knowledge is required to join the bootcamp. Participants will gain a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration. They will also learn about cloud security, penetration testing, and cyber threat intelligence analysis. The program covers topics like data loss prevention strategies, compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST, and risk management. Classes are held three times per week, and the class size is limited to 16 people. Upon completion, participants will receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit the website: https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop